WEBVTT

1
00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:59.000
<c.transcription>[WAKIZURE] Somo somo kore wa,</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] To begin with,)</c>

2
00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:04.000
<c.transcription>Ichijō-no-In ni tsukae tatematsuru.</c>
<c.translation>(I am in the service of the Emperor Ichijo.)</c>

3
00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:12.000
<c.transcription>Tachibana-no-Michinari to wa waga koto nari.</c>
<c.translation>(I am known as Tachibana no Michinari.)</c>

4
00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:22.000
<c.transcription>Sate mo mikado konya kidoku no go-reimu, mashimashite.</c>
<c.translation>(It so happens that his Lordship)</c>

5
00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:28.000
<c.transcription>Sanjō-no-Kokaji Munechika ni.</c>
<c.translation>(has this night had a portentous dream oracle.)</c>

6
00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:34.000
<c.transcription>Mi-tsurugi wo utaserarubeki to no</c>
<c.translation>(The Sanjo swordsmith Munechika)</c>

7
00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:43.000
<c.transcription>senji tadaima narikudarite sōrō hodo ni.</c>
<c.translation>(must be ordered to forge a blade.)</c>

8
00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:50.000
<c.transcription>Kono yoshi wo Munechika ni mōshi-tsukebaya to</c>
<c.translation>(I am on my way now to tell Munechika)</c>

9
00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:54.000
<c.transcription>zonji sōrō.</c>
<c.translation>(of this matter.)</c>

10
00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:25.000
<c.transcription>[WAKIZURE] Ika ni kono uchi ni Munechika no, watari sōrō ka.</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] Is Munechika at home ?)</c>

11
00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:38.000
<c.transcription>[WAKI] Tare nite watari, sōrōzo.</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] Who is it that has come here ?)</c>

12
00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:47.000
<c.transcription>[WAKIZURE] Kore wa senji nite sōrō.</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] I am a messenger from the Emperor.)</c>

13
00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:55.000
<c.transcription>Waga kimi Kon'ya fushimi no reimu, mashimashite.</c>
<c.translation>(His Majesty has had a marvelous oracle in a dream.)</c>

14
00:05:55.000 --> 00:06:05.000
<c.transcription>Mitsurugi wo utaserarubeki tono onkoto nari.</c>
<c.translation>(According to the oracle, you must forge a fine sword for him.)</c>

15
00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:11.000
<c.transcription>Tōtō tsukamatsuri sōrae.</c>
<c.translation>(Please comply with this order at once.)</c>

16
00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:24.000
<c.transcription>[WAKI] Senji kashikomatte uketamawari sōrō sarinagara.</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] While I certainly must agree to execute this imperial order, )</c>

17
00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:33.000
<c.transcription>Orifushi aizuchi utsubeki mono no naku sōrō wo ba,</c>
<c.translation>(as I do not have anyone to assist me,)</c>

18
00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:40.000
<c.transcription>nani to tsukamatsuri sōrō beki.</c>
<c.translation>(I do not know how I will be able to carry it out.)</c>

19
00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:46.000
<c.transcription>[WAKIZURE] Fushigi no koto wo mōsu mono kana.</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] What you say sir, seems most strange.)</c>

20
00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:53.000
<c.transcription>Sono na wo etaru, nanji naruga</c>
<c.translation>(To hear that someone of your reputation)</c>

21
00:06:53.000 --> 00:07:00.000
<c.transcription>aizuchi utsubeki mono no naki towa.</c>
<c.translation>(does not have an appropriate assistant,)</c>

22
00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:06.000
<c.transcription>Kokoroegataki iigotokana.</c>
<c.translation>(is the most unfortunate news.)</c>

23
00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:14.000
<c.transcription>[WAKI] Kore wa ōse nite sōrae domo,</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] Even though I am commanded to do so,)</c>

24
00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:23.000
<c.transcription>Kayō no ichidaiji no mono wo tsukamatsuru ni wa</c>
<c.translation>(without an assistant whose skills are equal to my own,)</c>

25
00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:34.000
<c.transcription>ware ni otonaru koto no mono no aizuchi, tsukamatsurite koso.</c>
<c.translation>(it will not be possible to fulfill this order)</c>

26
00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:42.000
<c.transcription>Mitsurugi wo mo uchimōsubekere.</c>
<c.translation>(to forge an imperial blade.)</c>

27
00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:50.000
<c.transcription>Tonikaku ni onpenji wo mōshikane.</c>
<c.translation>(This is the answer I must give,)</c>

28
00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:56.000
<c.transcription>Sekimenshitaru bakari nari.</c>
<c.translation>(though I am overcome with embarassment.)</c>

29
00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:03.000
<c.transcription>[WAKIZURE] Mōsu tokoro wa saru koto naredomo.</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] Even though it may be as you say,)</c>

30
00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:11.000
<c.transcription>Mikado mo fushigi no reimu mashimaseba.</c>
<c.translation>(yet as this is the Emperor's wonderful dream oracle,)</c>

31
00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:17.000
<c.transcription>Ikanaru koto ka sōrōbeki</c>
<c.translation>(it surely must be relied upon)</c>

32
00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:25.000
<c.transcription>tanomoshiku omoi mōshitsutsu</c>
<c.translation>(and you must quickly say)</c>

33
00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:33.000
<c.transcription>hayahaya ryōjō mōisubeshito</c>
<c.translation>(you will accept the order.)</c>

34
00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:42.000
<c.transcription>Kasanete senji arikereba.</c>
<c.translation>(Let me repeat the imperial command!)</c>

35
00:08:42.000 --> 00:09:10.000
<c.transcription>[WAKI] Kono ue wa tonimo kakunimo Munechika ga,</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] At this point, in any case, Munechika)</c>

36
00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:27.000
<c.transcription>[JIUTAI] Tonimo kakunimo Munechika ga,</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] In any case, Munechika)</c>

37
00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:38.000
<c.transcription>Shintai koko ni kiwamarite.</c>
<c.translation>(must here decide his course of action.)</c>

38
00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:55.000
<c.transcription>Mitsurugi no yaiba no midaruru kokoro narikeri.</c>
<c.translation>(Like the ripples beaten along a well-forged blade, his heart wavers.)</c>

39
00:09:55.000 --> 00:10:11.000
<c.transcription>Sarinagara goseitō sugunaru ima no miyo nareba,</c>
<c.translation>(Yet, as the reign in the present age is righteous,)</c>

40
00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:20.000
<c.transcription>Moshimo kidoku no ariyasen.</c>
<c.translation>(a miracle may well be afforded me.)</c>

41
00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:30.000
<c.transcription>Sore nomi tanomu kokoro kana.</c>
<c.translation>(I must place my trust only in this.)</c>

42
00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:45.000
<c.transcription>Sore nomi tanomu kokoro kana.</c>
<c.translation>(I must place my trust only in this.)</c>

43
00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:55.000
<c.transcription>[WAKIZURE] Senji ni makase tōtō mitsurugi wo tsukamatsuri sōrae.</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] Hurry! make the sword.)</c>

44
00:10:55.000 --> 00:11:00.000
<c.transcription>[WAKI] Kashikomatte sōrō.</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] Yes! sir.)</c>

45
00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:32.000
<c.transcription>[WAKI] Kore wa ichidaiji no koto wo, ōse idasarate sōrō monokana.</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] This is a great task you have come to give me.)</c>

46
00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:44.000
<c.transcription>Kayō no koto ni wa shinriki wo tanomu naradewa, bechigi naku sōrō.</c>
<c.translation>(Such a command can be carried out if I ask for divine help.)</c>

47
00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:56.000
<c.transcription>Soregashi ga uji no shin na Inari no, myōjin nite sōrō hodoni.</c>
<c.translation>(As my family deity is Inari no Myojin,)</c>

48
00:11:56.000 --> 00:12:04.000
<c.transcription>Kore yori sugu ni, Inari ni mairi. </c>
<c.translation>(I will go at once to Inari,)</c>

49
00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:15.000
<c.transcription>Kono koto kisei mōsabaya to zonji-sōrō.</c>
<c.translation>(and pray concerning this matter.)</c>

50
00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:52.000
<c.transcription>[SHITE] Nō nō are naru wa Sanjō no Kokaji Munechika nite, on iri sōrō ka.</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] Ho there! Is that the Swordsmith of Sanjō, Munechika ?)</c>

51
00:12:52.000 --> 00:13:02.000
<c.transcription>[WAKI] Fushigi ya na nabete narazaru on-koto naru ga.</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] How mysterious! Here is someone who is certainly not an ordinary person.)</c>

52
00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:10.000
<c.transcription>Michi mo naki kata yori kitaritamai</c>
<c.translation>(There is no path from the direction from which he has appeared,)</c>

53
00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:16.000
<c.transcription>waga na wo sashite notamō wa.</c>
<c.translation>(and now he has called me by name.)</c>

54
00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:24.000
<c.transcription>Ikanaru hito nite mashi-masu zo.</c>
<c.translation>(What manner of man are you ?)</c>

55
00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:34.000
<c.transcription>[SHITE] Kumo no ue naru kimi yori mo</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] You have been ordered)</c>

56
00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:44.000
<c.transcription>tsurugi wo uchite mairaseyo to</c>
<c.translation>(by his Imperial Majesty)</c>

57
00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:53.000
<c.transcription>nanji ni ōse ari shi yo nō.</c>
<c.translation>(to forge a sword!)</c>

58
00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:58.000
<c.transcription>[WAKI] Sareba koso, </c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] As I thought, you are not what you seem to be,)</c>

59
00:13:58.000 --> 00:14:08.000
<c.transcription>sore ni tsukete mo nao nao kidoku no on-koto nare.</c>
<c.translation>(and events must be of great importance indeed.)</c>

60
00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:14.000
<c.transcription>Tsurugi no choku mo tadaima naru wo.</c>
<c.translation>(I have just received the order to make a blade!)</c>

61
00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:21.000
<c.transcription>Hayaku mo shiroshimesaruru koto</c>
<c.translation>(How could it be that anyone could know so soon ?)</c>

62
00:14:21.000 --> 00:14:28.000
<c.transcription>Kaesu-gaesu mo fushin nari.</c>
<c.translation>(No matter how I consider it, the matter is most strange.)</c>

63
00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:38.000
<c.transcription>[SHITE] Geni geni sore wa saru koto naredomo</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] In truth, it is as you say. It is said: To know a thing one's self,)</c>

64
00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:46.000
<c.transcription>ware nomi shireba moro bito made mo.</c>
<c.translation>(it is to find it is known by all.)</c>

65
00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:52.000
<c.transcription>[WAKI] Ten ni koe ari.</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] A voice in heaven,)</c>

66
00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:58.000
<c.transcription>[SHITE] Chi ni hibiku.</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] echoes on the earth!)</c>

67
00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:03.000
<c.transcription>[JIUTAI] Kabe ni mimi:</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] Wall have ears:)</c>

68
00:15:03.000 --> 00:15:19.000
<c.transcription>Iwa no mono iu yo no naka ni,</c>
<c.translation>(In the world where rocks may speak,)</c>

69
00:15:27.000 --> 00:15:37.000
<c.transcription>Iwa no mono iu yo no naka ni,</c>
<c.translation>(In the world where rocks may speak,)</c>

70
00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:52.000
<c.transcription>Kakure wa araji koto ni nao,</c>
<c.translation>(and nothing is hidden,)</c>

71
00:15:52.000 --> 00:16:03.000
<c.transcription>kumo no uebito no mitsurugi no</c>
<c.translation>(nothing shall dim the radiance)</c>

72
00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:14.000
<c.transcription>hikari wa nanika kurakaran.</c>
<c.translation>(of the Emperor's sword.)</c>

73
00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:21.000
<c.transcription>Tada tonome kono kimi no</c>
<c.translation>(Only have faith)</c>

74
00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:31.000
<c.transcription>Meguni ni yoraba mitsurugi mo</c>
<c.translation>(that through his Majesty's grace and the sword)</c>

75
00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:40.000
<c.transcription>nado ka kokoro ni kanawazaru.</c>
<c.translation>(will be realized as you wish.)</c>

76
00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:55.000
<c.transcription>Nado ka wa kanawazarubeki.</c>
<c.translation>(It must be realized.)</c>

77
00:16:55.000 --> 00:17:09.000
<c.transcription>[JIUTAI] Sore Kan-nō sanseki no tsurugi</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] Once with such a blade, the Emperor's Three Foot Sword,)</c>

78
00:17:09.000 --> 00:17:18.000
<c.transcription>inagara Shii no midare wo shizume.</c>
<c.translation>(subdued the rebellion of the Ts'in by its reputation alone.)</c>

79
00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:25.000
<c.transcription>Mata Yō-tei ga Gei no tsurugi</c>
<c.translation>(Again, the Yang Emperor, with his sword Kei )</c>

80
00:17:25.000 --> 00:17:54.000
<c.transcription>Shiujt'n no hikari wo ubaeri.</c>
<c.translation>(outshone the brillance of the House of Chou.)</c>

81
00:17:56.000 --> 00:18:11.000
<c.transcription>[SHITE] Sono nochi Gensō Kō-tei no Shōki Daijin mo</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] In later years, the Emperor Huan Tsung's Minister Chung K'ei too,)</c>

82
00:18:11.000 --> 00:18:18.000
<c.transcription>[JIUTAI] Tsurugi no toku ni konpaku wa,</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] joined his spirit after death with the virtue of his sword,)</c>

83
00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:24.000
<c.transcription>kunpen ni tsukae-tatematsuri.</c>
<c.translation>(and thus served at his Lord's side.)</c>

84
00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:33.000
<c.transcription>Mōryō kijin ni itaru made </c>
<c.translation>(Even evil spirits and demons)</c>

85
00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:40.000
<c.transcription>tsurugi no yaiba no yaiba no hikari ni osorete,</c>
<c.translation>(were in fear of that sword's glow,)</c>

86
00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:50.000
<c.transcription>sono ada wo nasu koto wo ezu.</c>
<c.translation>(and the destruction they sought was not achieved.)</c>

87
00:18:50.000 --> 00:19:10.000
<c.transcription>[SHITE] Kanka honchō ni oite tsurugi no itoku</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] Indeed, the virtue of the swords in China and Japan)</c>

88
00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:35.000
<c.transcription>[JIUTAI] mōsu ni oyobanu kidoku to kaya.</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] and their miraculous power is beyond expression!)</c>

89
00:19:54.000 --> 00:20:09.000
<c.transcription>[JIUTAI] Mata waga chō no sono hajime</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] And so, it was in the early days of our history,)</c>

90
00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:27.000
<c.transcription>Ninnō jiunidai Keikō-tennō </c>
<c.translation>(the Twelfth of the Imperial Line, the Emperor Keikō,)</c>

91
00:20:27.000 --> 00:20:38.000
<c.transcription>miko no mikato no on-na wo ba</c>
<c.translation>(had a son known by the name)</c>

92
00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:51.000
<c.transcription>Yamata-dake to mōshishiga.</c>
<c.translation>(Yamato-dake.)</c>

93
00:20:51.000 --> 00:21:10.000
<c.transcription>Kiui wo Taiji no chiku wo uke.</c>
<c.translation>(The wild barbarians! he received the order to subdue them.)</c>

94
00:21:10.000 --> 00:21:23.000
<c.transcription>Seki no higashi mo harukanaru.</c>
<c.translation>(The barrier check points far behind as yet further to the East.)</c>

95
00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:36.000
<c.transcription>Azuma no tabi no michi sugara</c>
<c.translation>(The road of his journey to the Eastern provinces took him.)</c>

96
00:21:36.000 --> 00:21:54.000
<c.transcription>Ise ya Owari no umizura ni tatsu nami made mo </c>
<c.translation>(Even at Ise and Owari the waves on the sea rise and return!)</c>

97
00:21:54.000 --> 00:22:02.000
<c.transcription>kaeru koto yo to urayami</c>
<c.translation>(With envy he wondered always, )</c>

98
00:22:02.000 --> 00:22:13.000
<c.transcription>itsu ka warera mo kaeru nami no</c>
<c.translation>(when he too might find himslef, with foam-drenched sleeves)</c>

99
00:22:13.000 --> 00:22:34.000
<c.transcription>koromode ni arama shi to omoi-tsuzukete-yuku hodo ni.</c>
<c.translation>(returning home, even as he continued on his way.)</c>

100
00:22:34.000 --> 00:22:52.000
<c.transcription>[SHITE] Koko ya kashiko no tatakai ni</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] In the battles in one place and in the next )</c>

101
00:22:52.000 --> 00:23:03.000
<c.transcription>[JIUTAI] Jin-ba gankutsu ni mi wo kudaki,</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] Men and horses: their bodies crushed in their caverns,)</c>

102
00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:15.000
<c.transcription>Chi wa takuroku no kawa to natte,</c>
<c.translation>(their blood on the battlefields a river,)</c>

103
00:23:15.000 --> 00:23:28.000
<c.transcription>kōha tate nagashi sudo ni oyoberu Ebisu mo.</c>
<c.translation>(their shields swept away on crimson waves again and again.)</c>

104
00:23:28.000 --> 00:23:35.000
<c.transcription>kabuto wo nuide hoko wo fuse</c>
<c.translation>(Finally the barbarians removed their helmets,)</c>

105
00:23:35.000 --> 00:23:47.000
<c.transcription>mina kōsan wo mōshikeri.</c>
<c.translation>(lay down their arms and were made to surrender.)</c>

106
00:23:47.000 --> 00:24:10.000
<c.transcription>Mi-koto no gyō yori mi-kariba wo susume tamaeri.</c>
<c.translation>(From the time of this Prince's reign, the royal sport of hunting was begun.)</c>

107
00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:30.000
<c.transcription>Koro wa Kami-na-zuki,</c>
<c.translation>(It was an incident that occurred, )</c>

108
00:24:30.000 --> 00:24:39.000
<c.transcription>hatsu ka amari no koto nareba.</c>
<c.translation>(on the twentieth day of the Tenth month:)</c>

109
00:24:39.000 --> 00:24:48.000
<c.transcription>Yo-mo no momiji mo fuyugare no</c>
<c.translation>(Everywhere the autumn tints had faded,)</c>

110
00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:58.000
<c.transcription>tō-yama ni miyuru hatsu-yuki wo,</c>
<c.translation>(and even on the distant winter withered mountains,)</c>

111
00:24:58.000 --> 00:25:10.000
<c.transcription>nagame sase tamaishi ni,</c>
<c.translation>(the traces of the first snow fall could be seen.)</c>

112
00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:24.000
<c.transcription>[SHITE] Yebisu shi-hō wo kakomitsutsu.</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] The barbarians surrounding him on every side)</c>

113
00:25:24.000 --> 00:25:34.000
<c.transcription>[JIUTAI] Kare-no no kusa ni hi wo kake</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] Set fire to the grass of the withered fields, and as the blaze burned high)</c>

114
00:25:34.000 --> 00:25:44.000
<c.transcription>yo-en shikiri ni moe-kitari</c>
<c.translation>(and as the blaze burned high with heavy lingering billows of smoke.)</c>

115
00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:57.000
<c.transcription>kataki-seme-tsuzumi wo uchi-kakete </c>
<c.translation>(Began to beat their war drums in the signal to attack.)</c>

116
00:25:57.000 --> 00:26:12.000
<c.transcription>ka-en wo hanachite kakarikareba.</c>
<c.translation>(The Towering flames! as the attack blazed forward)</c>

117
00:26:12.000 --> 00:26:22.000
<c.transcription>[SHITE] Mi-koto tsurugi wo nuite...</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] The Prince drew his sword)</c>

118
00:26:22.000 --> 00:26:28.000
<c.transcription>[JIUTAI] Mi-koto tsurugi wo nuite,</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] The Prince drawing his sword,)</c>

119
00:26:28.000 --> 00:26:37.000
<c.transcription>atari wo harai tachimachi.</c>
<c.translation>(wielded it about him.)</c>

120
00:26:37.000 --> 00:26:44.000
<c.transcription>ni honō mo tachi-shirizoke to,</c>
<c.translation>(At once, the flames drew back,)</c>

121
00:26:44.000 --> 00:26:54.000
<c.transcription>shi-hō no kusa wo nagi-haraeba.</c>
<c.translation>(as it mowed down the grasses in all directions.)</c>

122
